body.description: Bye-bye blowouts, later leaks, hello Triple Dry Protection. Our most absorbent diapers ever have a U-shaped channel to whisk away wetness, an absorbent core and a breathable layer to circulate air to skin. Made with soft-touch material and a comfy, secure fit, they’re dermatologist tested, non-allergenic and come in almost-as-cute-as-baby patterns.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby Boy is growing fast
reviews.reviewText: Great diapers for a fast growing baby boy or girl! hardly any diaper rash whatsoever

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My favorite diapers
reviews.reviewText: My baby has slightly more narrow hips and no butt lol and so these diapers fit her better than any others we have tried they don’t bunch up and they absorb really well with no leaks she can even wear one overnight now that she sleeps through the night and we have no issues. These diapers are very soft on her sensitive skin and don’t rub or leave redness like other brands such as pampers pure or honest diapers do. These are my go to diapers now and the only ones I will purchase for my baby I love them!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love the function, hate the smell
reviews.reviewText: I had a sample of these diapers when my daughter was born along with a few others. We ended up preferring these over the more common brands. They have the gusset at the back that prevents most blowouts as well as larger ruffles around the legs that help do the same. We like how narrow they are in the crotch, as they bunch up less.The only issue I have after using these for a few months is that there is a very distinct, chemically smell to them. We actually ended up at the urgent care thinking our daughter had an UTI. All of the tests came back negative. It turns out my super-powered mommy nose was just picking up the smell of the diaper mixed with urine, as the smell goes away if we try a different brand on her.Now that I know it’s just the smell of the diapers, we’ll keep using these since they work great for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Must have diapers for my granddaughter
reviews.reviewText: My son and daughter-in-law swear by this brand of diapers. They have seen less diaper rashes, leaking and anything else that comes to mind. Sure, they are more expensive, but as the saying goes "You get what you pay for". Right now I am paying for these. Honestly, I have personally witnessed less waking up in the middle of the night, less crying due to soaking wet diapers, and most of all a happy baby, son, and daughter-in-law. The price is worth it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This updated diaper is inferior to the old Babyganics diapers. I have used Babyganics for over 6 years on on my three other children and am highly disappointed by these changes in the new diapers. They leak more often, are less absorbent, feel cheaper, and baby doesn’t like. I’ve been able to find a few packages of the original babyganic diapers, but will have to find natural alternatives in the future for my fourth baby. Very disappointed

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable, durable for baby; Chemical free, wetness indicator for parents.
reviews.reviewText: After trying a few different diaper brands, we began using Babyganics primarily due to the softness of the fabric and the durability we saw from the diapers. Couple this with the fact that they are made with plant based materials and have a wetness indicator unlike some other brands, and this is the winner.Terrific fit and full satisfaction from the product. If you value comfort for your baby and are interested in a more organic diaper alternative, Babyganics is the best option we have found out there.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not worth the money
reviews.reviewText: I bought these on prime day and was so excited to try them on my daughter. Then I opened the box and realized there’s no wetness indicator, they’re not very soft, the sizing runs small (she’s 16 lbs) and they feel cheap. These feel the same as the up and up brand diapers at target which are a quarter of the price. Very disappointing. Not worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Great in the beginning.
reviews.reviewText: These were fantastic in the beginning. My little girl had a lot of blowouts. However she’s 5 months old and they don’t hold anymore. Not sure why, but we have moved on to Huggies special delivery. They are soft on her skin and hold up.
Son pañales "sanos", ecológicos, buena relación calidad-precio y són ligeros a la vez que absorbentes.
